cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of embedding points in the plane and connecting them with various graphical features. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents ILP and FPT algorithms for the general problem and efficient algorithms for restricted versions of the problem. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with the problem of set membership and connectivity of points in the plane. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the problem of finding a planar realization with certain constraints. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper proves the NP-completeness of a special case of the problem.
